The Constitutional Court has dismissed Nehawu's application to appeal 2018 public sector salary ruling. eNCA speaks to Cosatu's first Deputy President Mike Shingange. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court has dismissed Nehawu's application to appeal a 2018 public sector salary ruling. READ: Unions, government face off in court over wage dispute The Labour Court previously ruled government did not have to abide by the 2018 multi-year deal. Government took the matter to court after saying it can't afford any hikes. Watch the video above for more details.